spans.text: the awful faces of other times
the noise of the battle been heard on thy banks
of the battle been heard on thy banks
Fingal in the mid of his host
roll on the path of the hunter
Carun's grassy banks , son of the cloudy night
white as the snow of Ardven
of Comhal fallen , chief of the mournful tale
the voice of the chief no more
have thought I saw him on the distant rock
I saw him on the distant rock
he would return with the night
of the king of the world
fall like the heart of the desert
love , to frighten and please my soul
a voice like the breeze of my hills
me hear the voice of Comala
OH lovely son of death ! — COME to the cave of my rest
the war of the ocean , and our hands
at the streams of my hills
the voice of the huntress of Galmal
with joy on the dreams of their rest
